main event: A witness observed a bright light in the sky near New Carlisle, Ohio for a few minutes in May 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared as a bright light, brighter than the brightest stars.
The object was visible for about 10 minutes before hazy fading away.
The object made a humming sound and was described as yellowish-white in color.
The witness estimated the object to be as large as the head of a match held at arm's length.
The witness drew a sketch showing an elongated object with an arrow indicating the direction of motion.
